🔷 Logging Levels (Best Practice ⭐)

Use different levels:

| Method | Purpose     |
| ------ | ----------- |
| log    | Normal info |
| warn   | Warning     |
| error  | Errors      |

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Environment-Based Logging

```javascript
if (process.env.NODE_ENV === "development") {
  console.log("Debug info");
}
```

✔ Avoid logs in production

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Using Logging Libraries

Popular tools:

* **Winston** → Advanced logging
* **Morgan** → HTTP logs
* **Debug** → Conditional logging

Install:

```bash
npm install winston
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Example: Structured Logging

```javascript
console.log({
  event: "user_login",
  user: "Saakshi",
  time: new Date()
});
```

✔ Better readability

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Debugging Async Code

```javascript
async function fetchData() {
  try {
    const data = await fetch("url");
    console.log(data);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(error);
  }
}
```

✔ Always handle errors

